content: We will now begin our nice lesson!

I also chose this move against Li
Here, he thought for a while again
to keep 2 active areas - right and lower.

so my left side future space is weaker now

where would you play next black move?
because, if he defends passively below

to get a stone on left
so the timing now was important
where would you play next black move?

but also consider about how to not let white come out to space with tempo
not let white ruin the black potential
black still keeps the space potential
what would you do now, as white?
this is a complicated situation for white, indeed.
If white wants to use the tactics of filling up the left space with tempo,
because if black is brave, and defends actively,
then white will make it just worse for himself
black will just get more stones into left space
and make sure of all dangers
so maybe black must be careful
if black is forced to g11
